&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:400;&quot;&gt;How can you help each woodwind section blend and each student feel more confident? How can you predict when students will be sharp or flat, and how can you help students maintain a good tone throughout a rehearsal? Empower students to listen and adjust their tuning on their own. In this session, Boise State University woodwind faculty discuss tone and tuning tips for flute, oboe, clarinet, saxophone, and bassoon. Learn techniques to apply across instruments and specific tips for each instrument, from embouchure adjustment to reed advice to alternate fingerings.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:400;&quot;&gt;Whether you are an experienced educator looking for a refresher or a new educator looking for some basics, and whether you teach beginners or advanced players, you will leave with concrete solutions to common student problems. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:400;&quot;&gt;Plus, you will take away a helpful “cheat sheet” of tips, techniques and tid bits to add to your woodwind teaching tool box.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
